          "The rulers spoke French. So did power.",
          "",
          "For three hundred years after 1066,",
          "the Norman aristocracy ran England",
          "without bothering to learn English.",
          "Law, government, war, religion, the",
          "kitchens of the great houses — all",
          "conducted in French. The peasants",
          "kept speaking English to each other.",
          "",
          "When the two languages finally merged,",
          "the split stayed. English kept Norman",
          "words for the things Normans did:",
          "accuse, govern, conquer, marry, feast.",
          "",
          "Tier 2 is that world. Six domains",
          "where French didn't just borrow into",
          "English — it took over completely."
